git config --global user.name "user_name"
git config --global user.email "email_id"


git init Repository_name
Initialized empty Git repository in /home/akshay/Mytest/.git/

cd Repository_name (<<This is a git repo>>)


vi Repositor_Detail.txt and enter detail about repository and save it


git add Repositor_Detail.txt

git commit -m "Repositor had Been created on some date"

create repository on GitHub and the some path is generated add it locally on your terminal like below 

git remote add origin https://github.com/user_name/Mytest.git


git push origin master


and done.